<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 12:56PM CDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central
Claiborne, northeastern Campbell and northwestern Union Counties
through 245 PM EDT...
At 156 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
La Follette, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
La Follette, Fincastle, Norris Lake and Big Ridge State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
